content.problemStatement:
The clear() method in ArrayList is used to remove all elements from the list, making it empty. This is useful when you want to reset or reuse an ArrayList without creating a new one.

---

**Example:**

```java
ArrayList fruits = new ArrayList<>();
fruits.add("Apple");
fruits.add("Banana");
fruits.add("Orange"); // till here fruits ArrayList have size 3

fruits.clear() // After calling fruits.clear(), the ArrayList will contain no elements

// You can verify this by checking fruits.isEmpty() which will return true, or fruits.size() which will return 0.
```

